<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<FrameLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#F1F6F9"
    tools:context=".fragments.lesson3.WhatIsItFragment">

    <androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:overScrollMode="never">
        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical">
            <LinearLayout
                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent"
                android:orientation="vertical">
                <Button
                    android:id="@+id/btn_tts"
                    android:text="Read Aloud"
                    android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                    android:background="@drawable/btn_secondary_button"
                    android:drawableStart="@drawable/ic_text_to_speech"
                    android:textAllCaps="false"
                    android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                    android:paddingStart="10dp"
                    android:paddingEnd="20dp"
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="48dp" />
            </LinearLayout>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/description_1"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                android:textColor="@color/black"
                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                android:text="Fractions look a little like division expressions, but they aren’t problems to be solved. They are a way of expressing an amount. Like numbers, fractions tell you how much you have of something. There are different kinds of fractions that you need to get acquainted with and be able to deal with utmost understanding.\n\nSimilar Fractions:\n\nSimilar fractions are fractions which have the same denominator. To add or subtract similar fractions, add or subtract the numerators and copy the common denominator. Simplify the resulting fraction, if possible."/>
            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/example_1"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent"
                android:contentDescription="example"
                android:layout_marginVertical="10dp"
                android:src="@drawable/lesson_1_sample_3" />
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/description_2"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                android:textColor="@color/black"
                android:text="Example 1:\n\nAdd: 3/6 + 1/6\n\n3+1 Add the numerators.\n\n4/6 Copy the common denominator.\n\nAnswer: 𝟐/𝟑 Simplify (Lowest Term). → 4÷2/6÷2 = 2/3\n\nExample 2:\n\nSubtract: 8/15 − 3/15\n\n8−3 Subtract the numerators.\n\n5/15 Copy the common denominator.\n\nAnswer:𝟏/𝟑 Simplify (lowest term). → 5÷5/15÷5 = 1/3" />
            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/example_2"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="250dp"
                android:layout_marginVertical="10dp"
                android:contentDescription="example"
                android:src="@drawable/lesson_1_sample_3_1" />
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/description_3"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                android:textColor="@color/black"
                android:text="Dissimilar Fractions:\n\nDissimilar fractions are fractions with different denominators. To add or subtract dissimilar fractions, find the Least Common Denominator or LCD. Then, rewrite each fraction into its equivalent fraction using the LCD. Add or subtract the numerators and write the sum or difference over the common denominator. Simplify the resulting fraction, if possible.\n\nExample 3:\n\nAdd: 1/4 + 2/6\n\n12 + 12 Determine the LCD.\n\n3/12 + 4/12 To get the equivalent fraction, divide the LCD by the denominator and multiply the answer/quotient by the numerator.\n\n3+4/12 Add the numerators over the common denominator.\n\nAnswer: 𝟕/𝟏2" />
            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/example_3"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="400dp"
                android:layout_marginVertical="10dp"
                android:contentDescription="example"
                android:src="@drawable/lesson_1_sample_3_2" />
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/description_4"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                android:textColor="@color/black"
                android:text="Example 4:\n\nAdd: 1/4 + 2/6\n\n12 + 12 Determine the LCD.\n\n3/12 + 4/12 To get the equivalent fraction, divide the LCD by the denominator and multiply the answer/quotient by the numerator.\n\n3+4/12 Add the numerators over the common denominator.\n\nAnswer: 𝟕/𝟏2" />
        </LinearLayout>
    </androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>
</FrameLayout>